Preparing Arduino with Adafruit MotorShield v.2 to control a polargraph

Install Arduino programming environment:
1. http://www.arduino.cc

Load the acam2 sketch onto the Arduino
1. Run Arduino IDE
2. Open acam2.ino: File->Open <src dir>/qacam/polargraph/acam2
3. First time: Install libraries to control Adafruit Motorshield V2
   Sketch->Include Library->Manage Libraries 
   a) AccelStepper
   b) Adafruit Motor Shield V2 Library
4. Verify code (click check under File menu)
5. Connect to Arduino: Tools->Port
   Choose port that identifies Arduino.
   Verify with: Tools->Get BoardInfo
6. Load code onto Arduino (click -> under Edit menu)
